import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot_offset_window_new(region):
    analyzer = CoronavirusAnalyzer(last_date=last_date, first_date=first_date, in_english=in_english)
    start_date = '2020-01-17'
    end_date = '2020-02-11'
    s_daily_diagnosed = analyzer.df_virus_daily_inc_injured[region][start_date: end_date].copy()
    s_daily_diagnosed.index = ['-'.join(i.split('-')[1:]) for i in s_daily_diagnosed.index]
    df_move_inc_corr = analyzer.df_move_inc_corr.loc[start_date: end_date, mentioned_regions].copy()
    df_move_inc_corr.index = ['-'.join(i.split('-')[1:]) for i in df_move_inc_corr.index]
    df_region = df_move_inc_corr[region].copy()
    df_region['offset + window'] = df_region['offset'] + df_region['window']
    arr = df_region['offset + window'].values
    not_nan_mask = ~np.isnan(arr)
    df_region_first_not_nan = df_region.loc[not_nan_mask].copy().iloc[:2]
    offsets = df_region_first_not_nan['offset'].tolist()
    windows = df_region_first_not_nan['window'].tolist()
    off_wins = df_region_first_not_nan['offset + window'].tolist()
    print('{} "offset" in first 2 days: {}'.format(region, offsets))
    print('{} "window" in first 2 days: {}'.format(region, windows))
    print('{} "offset + window" in first 2 days: {}'.format(region, off_wins))
    df_region['offset'].plot()
    df_region['window'].plot()
    df_region['offset + window'].plot()
    s_daily_diagnosed.plot(color='red', label='daily new diagnosed')
    plt.title(region)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.show()
    return offsets, windows, off_wins
